title: Coast to Coast AM - Aug 13 2013 - Veteran Issues - Superman's Le
description:
Date:	08-13-13
Host:	George Noory
Guests:	Larry Tye, Dannion Brinkley, Joyce Riley
News segment guests: Rosemary Ellen Guiley, Dr. Peter Breggin

Hours 1 & 2: The treatment of US veterans, and their high rate of suicide, is discussed first by author Dannion Brinkley, then by nurse and advocate Joyce Riley.

Hours 3 & 4: Larry Tye, discussed the history of Superman on the 75th anniversary of his introduction, who remains America's most enduring hero, and how he's influenced U.S. history and pop culture.
